asion of Korea 1592-98|publisher=Osprey Publishing Ltd}}\n* {{citation|last=Turnbull|first=Stephen|year=1998|title=The Samurai Sourcebook|publisher=Cassell & Co|isbn=978-1-85409-523-7}}\n* {{citation|last=Villiers|first=John|year=1980|title=SILK and Silver: Macau, Manila and Trade in the China Seas in the Sixteenth Century (A lecture delivered to the Hong Kong Branch of the Royal Asiatic Society at the Hong Kong Club. 10 June 1980). [http://sunzi1.lib.hku.hk/hkjo/view/44/4401436.pdf The HKUL Digital Initiatives]}}\n* {{citation|last=Yi|first=Min-woong|year=2004|title=Imjin Wae-ran Haejeonsa: ''The Naval Battles of the Imjin War'' [\uc784\uc9c4\uc65c\ub780 \ud574\uc804\uc0ac]|publisher=Chongoram Media [\uccad\uc5b4\ub78c\ubbf8\ub514\uc5b4]|isbn=978-89-89722-49-6}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n===Primary sources===\n* Li, Guang-tao [\u674e\u5149\u6fe4], The research of the Imjin Japanese crisis of Korea [\u671d\u9bae\u58ec\u8fb0\u502d\u4e82\u7814\u7a76], (Central research academy) \u4e2d\u592e\u7814\u7a76\u9662 [http://www.ihp.sinica.edu.tw/ttscgi/ttsweb?@@425171258#BOT].\n* The annals of King Seonjo [\u5ba3\u7956\u5be6\u9304]\n* \u4e2d\u8208\u8a8c\n* \u8d99\u6176\u7537, \u4e82\u4e2d\u96dc\u9304\n* [[Qian Shizheng]] (\u9322\u4e16\u6968), ''The Records of the eastern expedition'' (\u5f81\u6771\u5be6\u7d00)\n* [[Song Yingchang]] (\u5b8b\u61c9\u660c), ''The letter collections of the restoration management''. [\u7d93\u7565\u5fa9\u570b\u8981\u7de8]\n* Han, Woo-keun. ''The History of Korea''. Trans. Kyung-shik Lee. Ed. Grafton K. Mintz. Seoul: Eul-Yoo, 1970.\n* Lee, Ki-baik. ''A New History of Korea''. Trans. Edward W. Wagner and Edward J. Schultz. Seoul: Ilchokak, 1984.\n* Nahm, Andrew C. ''Introduction to Korean History and Culture''. Seoul: Hollym, 1993.\n* Sansome, George. ''A History of Japan''. Stanford: Stanford UP, 1961.\n* Yi, Sun-sin. ''Nanjung Ilgi: War Diary of Admiral Yi Sun-sin''. Trans. Tae-hung Ha. Ed. Pow-key Sohn. Seoul: Yonsei UP, 1977.\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Japanese invasions of Korea}}\n* [http://www.h4.dion.ne.jp/~room4me/korea/bunroku.htm Toyotomi Hideyoshi's Korean Invasions: the Bunroku Campaign (1592\u201393)]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070427072503/http://www.e-sunshin.com/e-sunshin/life/yimjin_04.jsp The Battles of Imjin Waeran] (in Korean)\n* [http://www.boseong51.net/user/ftp/free/LeeSS/IMJIN-War-Outbreak.html The Imjin Waeran] (in Korean)\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20071212084905/http://jinju.museum.go.kr/ Jinju National Museum] is dedicated to this topic. Information in English and Korean.\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070205073646/http://www.teachenglishinasia.net/the-imjinwaeran The Imjinwaeran] (in English)\n\n{{Joseon}}\n{{Ming dynasty topics}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Japanese Invasions Of Korea (1592-1598)}}\n[[Category:Anti-Japanese sentiment in Korea]]\n[[Category:Anti-Japanese sentiment in China]]\n[[Category:Japanese invasions of Korea (1592\u20131598)| ]]\n[[Category:Joseon dynasty]]\n[[Category:1590s in Japan]]\n[[Category:Japan\u2013Korea relations]]\n", "text_old": "{{redirect|Invasion of Korea|invasions of Korea during the Korean War|Korean War}}\n{{short description|Japanese invasions of Korea in the 1590s}}\n{{Infobox military conflict\n| conflict    = Japanese invasions of Korea\n| image       = [[File:Siege-of-Busanjin-1592.jpg|250px|border]]\n| caption     = The Japanese landing at [[Busan]]\n| date        = May 23, 1592 \u2013 December 16, 1598 ([[Gregorian Calendar]]);<br />April 13, 1592 \u2013 November 19, 1598 (Lunar calendar) {{clarify |date=February 2020 |reason= Which Lunar calendar?}} \n| place       = [[Korean Peninsula]]\n| result      = Korean and Chinese strategic victory<ref name=\"Lee 108\">{{cite book |last= Lee|first= Kenneth|date= January 1, 1997|title= Korea and East Asia: The Story of a Phoenix|url= https://books.google.com/books?id=XrZQs-6KswMC&pg=PA108&lpg=PA108&dq=japanese+defeat+1592-1598|location= |publisher= Greenwood Publishing Group|page= 108|isbn= 9780275958237|access-date= March 26, 2015}} \"Thus the Korea\u2013Japan War of 1592\u20131598 came to a conclusion, with the Japanese totally defeated and in full-scale retreat. The Korean victory did not come easily.\"</ref>\n*Withdrawal of Japanese armies following military stalemate<ref name=\"Turnbull, Stephen 1598, p. 87\">Turnbull, Stephen. Samurai Invasions of Korea 1592\u20131598, p. 87  \"Out of 500 Japanese\nships only 50 survived to limp home.\"</ref>\n| combatant1  = [[File:Flag_of_the_king_of_Joseon.svg|15px]] [[Joseon]]<br />[[File: Left-facing dragon pattern on Wanli Emperor's imperial robe.svg|15px]] [[Ming dynasty|Ming]]\n| combatant2  = [[File:Toyotomi mon.png|15px]] [[Azuchi\u2013Momoyama period|Toyotomi regime]]\n| commander1  = '''Joseon:'''<br />\n'''[[File:Flag_of_the_king_of_Joseon.svg|15px]] [[Seonjo of Joseon|King Seonjo]]'''<br/>[[File:Coat of Arms of Prince of Joseon.png|16px]] [[Gwanghaegun of Joseon|Prince Gwanghae]]<br/>[[Ryu Seong-ryong]]<br/>''[[Flag_of_the_king_of_Joseon.svg|15px]] [[Gwon Yul]]''<br/>'''[[Flag_of_the_king_of_Joseon.svg|15px]] [[Yi Sun-sin]]{{KIA}}'''<br/>'''[[Flag_of_the_king_of_Joseon.svg|15px]] [[Yi Eokgi]]{{KIA}}'''<br/>'''[[Flag_of_the_king_of_Joseon.svg|15px]] [[Won Gyun]]{{KIA}}'''<br/>[[Shin Rip]]{{KIA}}<br/>[[Kim Si-min]]{{KIA}}<br/>[[Song Sang-hyun (Joseon)|Song Sang-hyun]]{{KIA}}<br/>[[Go Gyeong-myeong]]{{KIA}}<br/>[[Kim Cheon-il]]{{KIA}}<br/>[[Jo Heon]]{{KIA}}<br/>[[Kim Myeong-won]]<br/>[[Yi Il]]<br/>[[Gwak Jae-u]]<br/>[[Jeong Gi-ryong]]<br/>[[Kim Deok-nyeong]]<br/>[[Yujeong]]<br/>[[Hyujeong]]<br/>[[Jeong Mun-bu]]<br/>[[Kim Chung-seon]]\n----\n'''Ming:'''<br />\n[[File: Left-facing dragon pattern on Wanli Emperor's imperial robe.svg|15px]] [[Wanli Emperor|Emperor Wanli]]<br/>[[Song Yingchang]]<br/>[[Yang Hao (Ming dynasty)|Yang Hao]]<br/>[[Li Rusong]]<br/>[[Xing Jie]]\n----\nListed above: '''Inspectors-general/field commanders'''<br />[[Yang Shaoxun]]<br/>[[Ma Gui (general)